Q2_1: Call a Tow Truck: Contact a towing service to get his car moved off the highway and request a ride to the nearest transportation hub.
Q2_2: Use a Rideshare App: Use a rideshare app like Uber or Lyft to request a ride directly to the airport.
Q2_3: Call a Taxi Service: Contact a local taxi service to pick him up from his location and take him to the airport.
Q2_4: Contact a Friend or Family Member: Call a friend or family member who might be available to pick him up and take him to the airport.
Q2_5: Check Public Transportation Options: Look up the nearest bus or train routes that could get him to the airport.
Q2_6: Flag Down a Passing Vehicle: If safe to do so, try to flag down a passing vehicle for assistance or a ride to the airport.
Q2_7: Walk to a Nearby Business: Walk to a nearby business or gas station to seek help or use their phone to arrange transportation.
Q2_8: Contact the Airline: Call the airline to explain the situation and see if there are any options for rescheduling or getting on a later flight if he misses the current one.
Q3_1: Double-Check Transactions: Review all transactions of the day to ensure there were no errors in recording sales, discounts, or returns.
Q3_2: Count the Cash Again: Recount the cash in the register to ensure there was no mistake in the initial count.
Q3_3: Check for Misplaced Money: Look around the register area to see if any money has fallen or been misplaced.
Q3_4: Review Security Footage: If available, check the security camera footage to identify any suspicious activities or errors.
Q3_5: Ask Employees: Talk to other employees who worked that day to see if they noticed anything unusual or if they can help account for the discrepancy.
Q3_6: Check Receipts and Records: Verify that all receipts match the recorded sales and that no receipts are missing.
Q3_7: Examine Recent Sales Promotions: Review any recent sales promotions or discounts that could have led to an incorrect calculation or missing amount.
Q3_8: Report the Issue: If the discrepancy cannot be resolved, report the issue to the bakery owner or higher management immediately and document all efforts made to find the missing money.
Q5_1: Stay Calm: Keep everyone calm to make rational decisions and avoid panic.
Q5_2: Stay Put: Remain in one place to make it easier for rescuers to find them, unless they are in immediate danger.
Q5_3: Signal for Help: Use available materials to create visible signals, such as SOS signs with rocks, reflective materials, or a smoky fire.
Q5_4: Ration Food and Water: Carefully ration their remaining food and water to last as long as possible.
Q5_5: Find Water: Locate a water source, such as a stream or river, and purify the water using tablets, boiling, or a filtration device if available.
Q5_6: Build a Shelter: Construct a shelter using natural materials to protect themselves from the cold and weather.
Q5_7: Keep Warm: Build a fire for warmth, signaling, and protection against wild animals. Ensure proper ventilation to avoid carbon monoxide poisoning.
Q5_8: Use Emergency Gear: Utilize any emergency gear they have, such as a compass, map, GPS device, or emergency beacon, to help signal for help or navigate to a safer location.
Q7_1: Use a Different Payment Method: If Sam has another credit card, debit card, or cash, he can use it to pay the bill.
Q7_2: Check Mobile Banking: Use a mobile banking app to transfer funds to the account linked to the declined credit card, if possible.
Q7_3: Call the Bank: Contact his bank to explain the situation and see if they can temporarily increase his credit limit or resolve the issue with the card.
Q7_4: Ask the Restaurant for Assistance: Speak to the restaurant manager to explain the situation and see if they can hold his ID while he arranges payment or returns with cash.
Q7_5: Ask the Neighbor for Help: Politely ask his date if they can cover the bill and assure them that he will repay them as soon as possible.
Q7_6: Use a Payment App: If both Sam and the restaurant accept mobile payment apps (like PayPal, Venmo, or Apple Pay), he can use those to pay.
Q7_7: Visit an ATM: If there's an ATM nearby, he can withdraw cash to pay the bill.
Q7_8: Offer Collateral: Offer to leave something of value (like a watch or phone) with the restaurant as collateral until he can return with payment.
